Debian Trixie desktop environment running XFCE over noVNC, packaged as a Docker container.
Provides a full graphical Debian desktop accessible directly from a web browser.

Features

Debian Trixie (testing)
XFCE desktop (with wallpaper + desktop icons)
Browser-based access via noVNC (no client required)
VNC password protected
Chromium web browser
Useful CLI tools included:
sudo, curl, wget
nano, less, tree
ip, ping, netstat
zip, unzip

unattended-upgrades enabled
Non-root debian user with sudo access

-------------------------------------------------

Amend passwords in Dockerfile

ARG ROOT_PASSWORD= # Root password
ARG DEBIAN_PASSWORD= # User (debian) password

-------------------------------------------------

Amend VNC password from default "debian" password
RUN mkdir -p /home/debian/.vnc && \
    x11vnc -storepasswd debian /home/debian/.vnc/passwd && \
    chown -R debian:debian /home/debian/.vnc

-------------------------------------------------

Location

debian-no-vnc/
├── Dockerfile
├── supervisord.conf
└── README.md

-------------------------------------------------

To create image - docker build -t debian-novnc .
To create container - docker run -d --name debian-novnc -p 6080:6080 debian-novnc
Accessibe via web browser - http://localhost:6080/